subtests.name: WebGL test #0: Structures with the same defination must be considered the same type.
WebGL test #1: Structures must have the same name to be considered the same type.
WebGL test #2: Structures must have the same sequence of type names to be considered the same type.
WebGL test #3: Structures must have the same field names to be considered the same type.
WebGL test #4: Structures must have the same type definitions to be considered the same type.
WebGL test #5: Structures must have the same type definitions (including precision) to be considered the same type.
WebGL test #6: Shaders with uniforms of unnamed struct type should compile and link successfully.
